
- React Component is devided into two Component
Component is the part of your website(User interface) such as header, sideNav, Main Content, and footer. 
Component can have another component or all of the component. basically, it is called as App Component or Root
Component is reusable, so you can use it in the another UI

1. Stateless Functional Component (also known as Dumb/Presentational.)
- it is basically fucntion which return the HTML, i.e the fucntion which return the <h1> tag. 
it can have props(properties) parameter of the fucntion
function welcome(props){
    return <h1>Hello, {props.name}</h1>
}

2. Statefull Class Component (also known as Smart/Container)
- it is class which extend component class, it has method render() which return the HTML, 
Class Component can receive props as parameter, the Class component example will be the following.
it has lifecycle hooks and private data(state)
class Welcome extends React.Component {
    render(){
        return <h1>Hello, {this.props.name}</h1>
    }
}

========================================================================
- Hooks
it lets you to use state and other react feature without writing a class. it is backaward compatible


- JSX (JavaScript XML)
it is extension to the JavaScript language syntax. we can Write XML-like code for elements and compoent. it make code simpler and more elegant
JSX tags also have a tag name, attribute and children like other XML. 

